{"lemma":"سَحِّ","slug":"سَحِّ","root":"س.ح.ح","root_slug":"س-ح-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ح-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19018","n19021","n19022"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rain pouring abundantly and extensively"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pour abundantly or flow forth vehemently and in consecutive quantities (upon)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to flog, to inflict whips on"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be fat to the utmost degree (said of bovids)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dates or in particular dates that are dry in such a manner that they dissolve well in the mouth","tags":["Yemen"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Unknown. Perhaps borrowed from Iranian. Compare Old Armenian ազոխ (azox, “unripe grapes”), Persian ازخ (azox, “rotten and empty nut”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19018","headword_ar":"سَحَّ","root":"sH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saH~N","text_ar":"سَحٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, &c.,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He poured out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K,) water, (S, A,) &c.: (S:) or, accord. to IDrd,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saH~N","text_ar":"سَحٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pouring out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth, in consecutive quantities:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to the Msb, [but this art. is not in my copy of that work,] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pouring forth much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundantly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the like is said in the Jámi' of Kz. (TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saH~ati Als~amaA='u maTarahaA","text_ar":"سَحَّتِ السَّمَا=ءُ مَطَرَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sky poured forth its rain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) See also an ex. of the inf. n. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saH~aA='u","text_ar":"سَحَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below. ―         -b2-  [Hence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisotano$adotuhu qaSiydapF fasaH~ahaA EalaY~a","text_ar":"اِسْتَنْشَدْتُهُ قَصِيدَةً فَسَحَّهَا عَلَىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I asked him to recite an ode, and he poured it forth to me;"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon me"},{"kind":"text","text":"], inf. n. as above. (A.) ―         -b3-  [Hence likewise,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saH~N","text_ar":"سَحٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (assumed tropical:)  The act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flogging."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saH~ahu miAy^apa sawoTK","text_ar":"سَحَّهُ مِايَةَ سَوْطٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (TA,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He inflicted upon him a hundred stripes of a whip."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) ―         -b4-  And (assumed tropical:)  The act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beating, striking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smiting."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b5-  And (assumed tropical:)  The act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thrusting"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piercing"},{"kind":"text","text":"[with a spear or the like]. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saH~a","text_ar":"سَحَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) so says Fei, or, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with analogy, (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saH~N","text_ar":"سَحٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suHuwHN","text_ar":"سُحُوحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or the former is the inf. n. of the trans. verb, and the latter is that of the intrans., (MF,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It flowed from above;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it flowed down;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] said of water, (S,) and of rain, and of tears; (S, A;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasaHosaHa","text_ar":"تَسَحْسَحَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tsH~H","text_ar":"تسحّح","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saH~a","text_ar":"سَحَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies, or signifies also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it poured out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth, vehemently:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tsHsH","text_ar":"تسحسح","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it flowed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of water, (S, TA,) and of a thing. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saH~ati Al$~aApu","text_ar":"سَحَّتِ الشَّاةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albaqarapu","text_ar":"البَقَرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasiH~u","text_ar":"تَسِحُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) or, accord. to Lh and Z,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasuH~u","text_ar":"تَسُحُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saH~N","text_ar":"سَحٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suHuwHN","text_ar":"سُحُوحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A,) or both, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suHuwHapN","text_ar":"سُحُوحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Ibn-Et-Teiyánee, TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the animal of the ox-kind, became fat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, AHn, S, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became fat to the utmost degree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became fat so as to flow with grease:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became fat, but not to the utmost degree."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","TA","K","MF","AZ","AHn"]},{"entry_id":"n19021","headword_ar":"سَحٌّ","root":"sH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"Rain"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pouring abundantly and extensively:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sbT","text_ar":"سبط"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHosaAHN","text_ar":"سَحْسَاحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHosaHN","text_ar":"سَحْسَحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) rain"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pouring vehemently,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, * TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"paring the surface of the earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHuwHN","text_ar":"سَحُوحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to rain that falls in large drops,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pouring much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundantly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also applied to a thundering cloud, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Han~aAnapN","text_ar":"حَنَّانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHaAbapN fiyhaA raEodN","text_ar":"سَحَابَةٌ فِيهَا رَعْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or, accord. to the S and A, to any cloud,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHaAbap","text_ar":"سَحَابَة"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pouring forth much rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 391: [in which it is said that in the latter case it may be proper; and in the former case, tropical:]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayonN saHosaAHapN","text_ar":"عَيْنٌ سَحْسَاحَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", so in a copy of the K, [and thus in my MS. copy of it,] in other copies ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saH~aAHapN","text_ar":"سَحَّاحَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", but the former is the right, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an eye pouring forth tears abundantly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaEonapN musaHosiHapN","text_ar":"طَعْنَةٌ مُسَحْسِحَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a spear-wound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowing"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with blood"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalifN saH~N","text_ar":"حَلِفٌ سَحٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A swearing in which oaths pour forth consecutively."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)       -A2-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qasobN","text_ar":"قَسْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tough, dates, that crumble in the mouth and have hard stones"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (K:) Az relates his having heard the Bahránees thus term a certain kind of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qasob","text_ar":"قَسْب"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scattered dates:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tough, dates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not sprinkled with water"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in order that they may stick together, for thus they do for this purpose, or they sprinkle the palm-leaf-receptacle of the dates for this purpose], (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scattered"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the ground, not collected in a receptacle, and not packed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suH~N","text_ar":"سُحٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IDrd, K,) which is of the dial. of El-Yemen. (IDrd.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","A","IDrd"]},{"entry_id":"n19022","headword_ar":"سُحٌّ","root":"sH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next precedes."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}